Caption: Fig. 1. Example pages of the initial prototype of PROACT. In this proto- type, all visualizations are made interactive to allow the users to explore the temporal dimension.
Fig. 2. Example pages of the revised prototype of PROACT. In this prototype, the temporal dimension has been “flattened” and the visual- izations are no longer interactive.

Fig. 3. Page 9. This is a summary page in the revised prototype showing all the information in the tool in a condensed form. The purpose is for the page to be printed and given to the patient to take home.
